00:50.009 --> 00:51.927
Good morning, Belly.

00:52.011 --> 00:53.596
[sniffles] Oh, my God.
Am I late?

00:53.679 --> 00:55.306
No, you're fine.

00:56.974 --> 00:58.559
Are you ready for your big day?

00:59.602 --> 01:00.644
Not at all.

01:00.728 --> 01:02.271
Oh, yes, you are.

01:02.354 --> 01:04.815
- What if I trip?
- You won't.

01:04.899 --> 01:07.526
Just hold on to Jeremiah's arm.

01:07.610 --> 01:08.819
He won't let you fall.

01:08.903 --> 01:10.863
- [laughs softly] That's true.
- You know,

01:10.946 --> 01:12.782
I still can't believe
you got him to go with you.

01:12.865 --> 01:15.868
He swore up and down he'd never
go to one of these things.

01:15.951 --> 01:18.162
[chuckles] He said
he doesn't mind.

01:18.245 --> 01:20.206
Well, he'd do anything for you.

01:20.289 --> 01:21.999
They both would.

01:26.295 --> 01:27.505
Everything okay?

01:28.547 --> 01:29.590
Yeah.

01:31.300 --> 01:33.219
Did I push you into this?

01:33.301 --> 01:34.720
Y-You can tell me the truth.

01:34.804 --> 01:37.932
- Um, maybe? A little, at first.
- Ugh...

01:38.015 --> 01:39.975
No, but I-I wanted
to make you happy.

01:40.059 --> 01:42.061
Look, honestly, we don't
even need to go tonight

01:42.144 --> 01:43.479
if you don't want to, okay?

01:43.562 --> 01:44.939
No, I-I want to go.

01:45.021 --> 01:46.774
I want to finish what I started.

01:46.857 --> 01:50.319
And I'm-I'm kind of proud
to show everybody.

01:51.445 --> 01:53.072
[laughs softly]

01:55.282 --> 01:58.452
I love you so much,
beautiful girl.

01:58.536 --> 02:00.246
[chuckles]

02:00.329 --> 02:02.790
- Okay, um...
- [both laugh]

02:02.873 --> 02:05.835
When they take your photograph,
remember, say "prune."

02:05.918 --> 02:08.002
It'll make your cheekbones
look divine.

02:08.086 --> 02:09.463
- Prune?
- Prune.

02:09.547 --> 02:11.632
It's just an old trick
I learned from Madonna.

02:11.715 --> 02:13.884
Or was it the Olsen twins?

02:13.968 --> 02:15.761
Who are they?

02:17.096 --> 02:19.640
They're moguls.
They're fashion icons.

02:19.723 --> 02:21.475
They owned the early 2000s.

02:21.559 --> 02:23.477
They're sisters
with the Scarlet Witch.

02:23.561 --> 02:25.646
- Oh.
- [laughs] Yeah, okay.

02:25.728 --> 02:27.565
Okay, now, meet me downstairs.

02:27.648 --> 02:29.483
There's a surprise for you.

02:33.362 --> 02:35.364
♪ ♪

02:39.952 --> 02:41.620
[laughs]

02:41.704 --> 02:44.290
You got me the dress I wanted?

02:46.292 --> 02:48.335
[laughs]
Thank you.

02:48.418 --> 02:50.254
Thank you, thank you.
Oh, my God.

02:50.337 --> 02:51.463
Thank your mom.

02:51.547 --> 02:53.632
It was her idea.

02:53.716 --> 02:55.050
I'm gonna check on your shoes.
I put them in the freezer...

02:55.134 --> 02:56.343
- Okay.
- ...to stretch them out.

02:58.804 --> 03:01.473
I can't believe you guys
got me the dress.

03:01.557 --> 03:03.475
You just looked so uncomfortable
in the other one.

03:04.560 --> 03:05.811
[laughs] I-I...

03:05.895 --> 03:07.438
I didn't think you noticed.

03:07.521 --> 03:09.773
I'm your mother.

03:11.025 --> 03:12.735
I know you.

03:17.990 --> 03:20.326
I-I know you didn't
want me to be a deb.

03:20.409 --> 03:22.244
I didn't, but...

03:27.249 --> 03:29.126
It's just hard to let you go.

03:38.761 --> 03:40.179
Steven, what are you doing here?

03:41.263 --> 03:43.140
I screwed up big-time.

03:48.187 --> 03:51.815
- Okay.
- So, poker with Liam, um...

03:53.359 --> 03:55.110
I lost every hand.

03:55.194 --> 03:57.738
You know, the money I've been
saving up all summer, it's gone.

03:57.821 --> 03:59.365
I can't even pay for my tux now.

04:00.658 --> 04:02.493
I'm sorry, I can't go
to the ball with you.

04:04.203 --> 04:06.455
- Are you fucking kidding me?
- I mean, I started losing

04:06.538 --> 04:08.457
a-and I thought I could win
it back, but every hand I got,

04:08.540 --> 04:09.959
things just got worse
and worse and worse.

04:10.042 --> 04:12.002
And you couldn't
just get up and leave?

04:13.963 --> 04:16.173
No, of course not,
'cause you wanted Liam

04:16.255 --> 04:18.634
and the other guys
to think you were a baller.

04:18.716 --> 04:21.053
You didn't think about
how it'd make me feel.

04:21.136 --> 04:22.846
Shayla, I am so sorry.

04:22.930 --> 04:24.390
Steven, the ball is tonight.

04:24.473 --> 04:25.975
I know.

04:27.643 --> 04:29.269
Fine, I'll just
give you the money.

04:29.353 --> 04:32.815
No, no, no, look, I'm not
taking any money from you.

04:32.898 --> 04:35.025
What about your mom?

04:35.109 --> 04:36.777
My mom, she'll kill me.

04:36.860 --> 04:39.029
Yeah, like I'm about
to kill you right now?

04:42.866 --> 04:45.327
Steven, please
just be honest with me.

04:45.411 --> 04:47.287
Do you even want to go
to this ball together?

04:47.371 --> 04:48.747
Yes. Yes, yes.

04:48.831 --> 04:50.582
I'm s... More than anything.

04:51.834 --> 04:53.669
Okay, I think my dad
has an old tux upstairs.

04:53.752 --> 04:54.962
You can wear that.

04:56.213 --> 04:58.298
I mean, will it, will it fit?

04:58.382 --> 04:59.675
Y-You know, 'c...

04:59.758 --> 05:01.969
No. No, n... No, no, no.
I'm... You're right.

05:02.052 --> 05:03.595
You're right. You're right.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

05:03.679 --> 05:07.016
That... That would be amazing.
That's super nice of you.

05:09.018 --> 05:12.312
Shayla, I really don't
want to miss this.

05:13.355 --> 05:15.107
You are a dumbass.

05:15.190 --> 05:16.608
[chuckles] Yeah. Yeah.

05:16.692 --> 05:18.569
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:23.282 --> 05:25.409
Hey, good morning. I, um...

05:25.492 --> 05:28.037
I picked up
some of those good muffins.

05:31.081 --> 05:32.332
[Belly] I...

05:32.416 --> 05:34.043
I'm good. Thanks, though.

05:34.126 --> 05:36.086
- Okay.
- [Susannah] Oh, Belly,
you should get going.

05:36.170 --> 05:38.756
Oh, and everyone,
stay out of the family room.

05:38.839 --> 05:40.758
I've done all your paintings

05:40.841 --> 05:42.676
and tonight after the ball,
we'll have a big unveiling.

05:42.760 --> 05:45.637
- Uh, can you put that
in Laurel's car, honey?
- Yeah. Yeah.

05:45.721 --> 05:48.057
- Hurry, hurry.
- Yeah, aren't-aren't
you driving me?

05:48.140 --> 05:50.808
I'm going over with Susannah,
so I thought

05:50.893 --> 05:52.478
maybe you could drive yourself.

05:52.561 --> 05:54.688
- Seriously?
- It's only a few blocks.

05:54.772 --> 05:57.232
- Unless you don't want to?
- Yes, yes. Yes.

05:57.316 --> 05:59.109
Drive slow, obey the lights,
wait four seconds

05:59.193 --> 06:00.944
- at each stop sign.
- I know, I know.

06:01.028 --> 06:02.362
- [Susannah] We'll see you
at the club in a few hours.
- Yep.

06:02.446 --> 06:04.698
- Hey.
- Yeah?

06:04.782 --> 06:05.824
Break a leg.

06:05.908 --> 06:06.992
That'd be bad.

06:07.076 --> 06:08.410
I'm supposed to be
dancing all night.

06:08.494 --> 06:10.162
I just... I just mean good luck.

06:10.245 --> 06:12.372
It's, like, a thing
people say. Um...

06:14.500 --> 06:18.128
For what it's worth,
Jere was the right choice.

06:19.213 --> 06:20.839
Yeah, I know.

06:23.675 --> 06:25.344
[door opens]

06:28.388 --> 06:29.723
[exhales]

06:29.807 --> 06:31.016
[car door closes]

06:37.064 --> 06:39.650
Don't be nervous. We're gonna be
the best waltzers out there.

06:39.733 --> 06:42.528
No, it's... it's not that.

06:42.611 --> 06:44.905
What? You nervous
about seeing the girls?

06:44.988 --> 06:47.282
No, I mean, everyone must know
what happened by now.

06:47.366 --> 06:49.284
They all probably hate me.

06:49.368 --> 06:50.494
Want me to come with?

06:50.577 --> 06:52.913
I could be your
hairstylist/bodyguard.

06:52.996 --> 06:55.582
No, you can't be in
the green room. It's girls-only.

06:56.875 --> 07:00.462
Listen, Belly, you've got this.

07:00.546 --> 07:02.005
All right?

07:02.089 --> 07:04.341
I'll be right by your side
the whole night.

07:04.424 --> 07:06.176
And if anybody gives you shit,

07:06.260 --> 07:08.387
- I will...
- You'll do what?

07:10.013 --> 07:12.766
I'll be like,
"Yo, that's not cool at all."

07:12.850 --> 07:14.101
- Mm-hmm. [laughs]
- I'll grab your hand,

07:14.184 --> 07:16.145
and we'll dance away
from everybody.

07:20.107 --> 07:21.733
[vehicle approaches]

07:23.819 --> 07:25.154
I'll see you at the club.

07:25.237 --> 07:26.613
Drive safe.

07:33.871 --> 07:35.372
What the freak?
Are you kidding me?

07:35.455 --> 07:38.332
- You and Jeremiah?
- It just happened.

07:38.417 --> 07:39.877
W-When? What, just now?

07:39.960 --> 07:42.045
Like, a-a week ago?

07:42.129 --> 07:45.174
Oh, my G... Are you kidding?

07:45.257 --> 07:49.011
[coughs] Oh, oh, t-this is sick.
I feel like I'm gonna throw up.

07:49.094 --> 07:50.846
Oh, oh, my God, and you guys
were, like, wh... like, what,

07:50.929 --> 07:52.306
like, sneaking around,

07:52.389 --> 07:53.932
keeping it a secret
from me this whole time?

07:54.016 --> 07:56.226
This has nothing
to do with you, Steven.

07:56.310 --> 07:57.436
Oh, my God, are you guys,
like, a couple?

07:57.519 --> 07:58.770
No! No, I don't, I don't know.

07:58.854 --> 08:00.898
We just... We-we just
kissed a few times.

08:00.981 --> 08:03.066
Just a f...
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

08:03.150 --> 08:04.484
So-so what about Conrad?

08:04.568 --> 08:06.737
- What about him?
- Uh, I don't know,

08:06.820 --> 08:09.114
maybe the fact that you've been,
like, goo-goo gaga over him

08:09.198 --> 08:11.241
- since you were ten.
- Well, I'm not ten anymore.

08:11.325 --> 08:13.160
- Yeah, not far from it.
- Really?

08:13.243 --> 08:15.370
Because Shayla's my age,

08:15.454 --> 08:18.248
which makes her a kid, too,
and that makes you a dirtbag.

08:18.332 --> 08:20.209
Oh, and you know who else
is my age? Taylor.

08:20.292 --> 08:21.919
- You hypocrite.
- Yeah, okay, okay, okay.

08:22.002 --> 08:23.212
Okay, I get it.

08:25.214 --> 08:26.215
I ju... I just...
I just don't want things

08:26.298 --> 08:28.300
to get all screwed up.

08:28.383 --> 08:30.594
All right, come on,
they're like our family, Belly.

08:30.677 --> 08:32.721
This affects, like,
way more than just you.

08:32.804 --> 08:34.972
I know.

08:35.057 --> 08:37.267
But you don't get
a say in who I date.

08:39.269 --> 08:42.272
I get to pick,
and I pick Jeremiah.

08:44.274 --> 08:46.276
You're just gonna
have to trust me.

08:49.988 --> 08:51.198
[car door opens]

09:00.249 --> 09:01.667
[whispers] Yeah, baby.

09:03.669 --> 09:05.212
[engine starts]

09:05.295 --> 09:06.838
[exhales]

09:06.922 --> 09:08.340
Here we go.

09:25.023 --> 09:26.984
[Steven] Hey.

09:27.067 --> 09:28.610
- Yo, what's up?
- You couldn't bother

09:28.694 --> 09:30.195
to tell me you were
hooking up with my sister?

09:30.279 --> 09:32.948
- She told you?
- No, I saw you guys kissing.

09:33.031 --> 09:35.284
[chuckles] Y-You're not gonna
beat me up, are you?

09:35.367 --> 09:37.786
- Oh, I'm really
thinking about it.
- Listen, Steven,

09:37.869 --> 09:39.997
- I-I really like her.
- Dude, you like
a lot of people.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.082
Have you seen me hooking up with
any guy or girl this summer?

09:42.165 --> 09:44.418
Yes, dude, I saw you making out
with that guy at Nicole's party.

09:45.585 --> 09:47.337
Okay, but that was,
like, a month ago.

09:47.421 --> 09:50.424
Listen, Steven, I would never
do anything to ever hurt her.

09:50.507 --> 09:52.759
I swear. Come on, it's Belly.

09:56.888 --> 09:58.974
Well, you still
should've told me.

10:00.017 --> 10:01.601
I should have.

10:01.685 --> 10:03.186
I'm sorry.

10:09.568 --> 10:12.904
God, just, don't do stuff
in front of me.

10:18.744 --> 10:20.746
[♪ Shana Falana: "Go Higher"]

10:31.965 --> 10:34.926
- No, no, come here. Hey.
- I don't think so, but, like...

10:35.010 --> 10:37.262
Ugh, I just
fucked up my eyeliner.

10:37.346 --> 10:39.097
Does anyone have
a razor I can borrow?

10:39.181 --> 10:41.308
- Got you.
- Thank you, angel.

10:41.391 --> 10:43.393
[Gigi] Thank you.

10:45.103 --> 10:47.564
[Shayla] Belly, you're here.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.232
- Come, I saved you a spot.
- [chuckles]

10:55.072 --> 10:56.782
[Shayla] Hey.

10:56.865 --> 10:58.700
You guys should really talk.

11:02.871 --> 11:05.415
Nicole, I'm-I'm really sorry.

11:05.499 --> 11:08.293
About what? Conrad?

11:08.377 --> 11:10.420
I'm over it.
I'm here with somebody else.

11:11.671 --> 11:13.298
Can I just explain
what happened?

11:14.966 --> 11:16.385
[sighs]

11:17.427 --> 11:18.804
[exhales]

11:18.887 --> 11:21.765
I've had a crush on Conrad
for, like, my whole life,

11:21.848 --> 11:25.727
and he's always just seen me
as-as his little sister.

11:26.937 --> 11:28.480
And then I thought
that, this summer,

11:28.563 --> 11:30.065
maybe he could like me back.

11:32.067 --> 11:35.654
But the thing is, what he liked
was that I liked him.

11:35.737 --> 11:37.531
You know, he never
actually liked me.

11:40.367 --> 11:41.660
And I'm sorry

11:41.743 --> 11:45.831
I was stupid enough
to think that he ever could.

11:45.914 --> 11:48.708
It's not your fault
Conrad's a fuckboy.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.337
But you're kind of
a fuckgirl, too.

11:53.839 --> 11:56.675
Cam, Conrad, now Jeremiah.

11:56.758 --> 11:58.969
You're playing
with a lot of hearts, Belly.

11:59.052 --> 12:03.390
Okay, maybe I was being
a little fuckgirl-ish,

12:03.473 --> 12:07.269
but I-I swear to you, Nicole,
I am completely over Conrad.

12:07.352 --> 12:09.521
Like, so, so over him.

12:09.604 --> 12:14.151
No one ever really
gets over their first love.

12:14.234 --> 12:16.278
♪ Serve others, you will gain ♪

12:16.361 --> 12:18.905
♪ Earth below, sky above ♪

12:18.989 --> 12:21.074
♪ Fill the darkness with love ♪

12:21.158 --> 12:24.077
♪ Morning sun will take pain ♪♪

12:24.161 --> 12:25.579
- Thanks, Steven.
- Yeah, of course.

12:25.662 --> 12:27.247
[indistinct chatter]

12:27.330 --> 12:28.874
My handsome date.

12:28.957 --> 12:30.876
- [laughs]
- Mom.

12:30.959 --> 12:32.294
- Good evening.
- I just need those...

12:32.377 --> 12:33.587
Here you go. Thank you.

12:36.840 --> 12:38.675
[Susannah] Look at us.

12:40.635 --> 12:42.387
It's perfect.

12:42.471 --> 12:44.222
Mom, you're not
gonna cry, are you?

12:44.306 --> 12:46.349
What, and ruin
my makeup? No way.

12:46.433 --> 12:48.351
It's just...

12:48.435 --> 12:50.896
Everything's gonna be
different next year.

12:50.979 --> 12:53.398
Conrad's going off to college.

12:53.482 --> 12:55.609
Yep.

12:55.692 --> 12:57.903
It may be the last summer
we're all together.

13:00.113 --> 13:02.115
Just don't forget I get
a dance from you tonight.

13:04.868 --> 13:06.369
[Susannah laughs]

13:06.453 --> 13:08.622
Ooh.

13:08.705 --> 13:09.831
Oh.

13:09.915 --> 13:11.291
Oh, Mom, you okay?

13:11.374 --> 13:13.210
Yeah, no, it's just, uh...

13:13.293 --> 13:14.419
it's been way too long
since I danced.

13:14.503 --> 13:16.546
I, um, must be out of practice.

13:16.630 --> 13:19.549
- Come on, um,
we should go inside.
- Yeah.

13:21.134 --> 13:22.552
[exhales]

13:24.554 --> 13:26.556
- [Steven] Come on, Mom.
- Thank you.

13:32.604 --> 13:34.606
♪ ♪

13:44.407 --> 13:45.909
[indistinct chatter]

13:45.992 --> 13:47.702
Is this our table? Yeah.

13:57.045 --> 13:58.713
[exhales]

13:58.797 --> 14:01.299
[John] Here and there, you know.

14:04.302 --> 14:05.971
I see you guys found the bar.

14:06.054 --> 14:08.306
[John] Yeah, it's the only way
I can get through

14:08.390 --> 14:10.058
this strange medieval ceremony.

14:10.141 --> 14:12.269
- [soft laughter]
- Where's Victoria?

14:12.352 --> 14:15.772
Oh, she had a last-minute
silent retreat to go to.

14:15.855 --> 14:17.232
This is nicer than our wedding.

14:18.567 --> 14:20.318
Our wedding was in
my parents' church basement.

14:20.402 --> 14:23.029
Anything is nicer
than our wedding.

14:23.113 --> 14:24.906
And I was four months pregnant.

14:24.990 --> 14:26.533
Ooh. Scandal.

14:26.616 --> 14:28.618
In the Korean Church? [chuckles]

14:28.702 --> 14:30.787
We had to tell everyone
that Steven was a preemie.

14:30.870 --> 14:33.248
Whenever we visit my parents,
my mom still gets tears

14:33.331 --> 14:34.665
in her eyes
saying she can't believe

14:34.749 --> 14:36.251
how strong and healthy he is.

14:36.334 --> 14:40.088
- [laughs]
- Here comes
our miracle baby now.

14:40.171 --> 14:41.840
Hey, Dad.

14:41.923 --> 14:43.967
- Come here. Good to see you.
- [grunts]

14:44.050 --> 14:45.719
- Did you bring the cuff links?
- Yes, I did.

14:45.802 --> 14:48.305
- [Steven] Thank you.
- Hi, Steven.

14:48.388 --> 14:50.640
Uh, I don't think we've
officially met. I'm Cleveland.

14:51.725 --> 14:52.892
Uh, hi.

14:54.185 --> 14:55.729
So, uh, your mom

14:55.812 --> 14:58.273
says that you got your sights
set on Princeton?

14:58.356 --> 15:01.568
Oh, uh, well, they-they
want me to stay in state.

15:01.651 --> 15:04.195
- [chuckles]
- If he gets into Princeton,

15:04.279 --> 15:06.114
we'll find a way
to make it work.

15:07.949 --> 15:09.242
Really?

15:11.244 --> 15:12.370
Thanks, Mom.

15:12.454 --> 15:14.664
- You look so handsome.
- Ah, d...

15:14.748 --> 15:17.208
Look, it's all...
all eyes on Shayla tonight.

15:17.292 --> 15:18.668
I'm-I'm just the arm candy.

15:18.752 --> 15:21.004
Um, but speaking of which,

15:21.087 --> 15:22.297
I should,
I should probably go up.

15:22.380 --> 15:24.841
- Uh, it was nice meeting you.
- Yeah.

15:24.924 --> 15:26.926
[♪ Ariana Grande:
"Thank U, Next"]

15:31.973 --> 15:34.976
♪ Thought I'd end up with Sean,
but he wasn't a match...

15:35.060 --> 15:37.729
[Belly] Girls aren't supposed
to know if we're pretty or not.

